description.narrative: (Jordan): USAID works in all governorates in Jordan to enhance the quality of and access to reproductive, maternal, newborn, and child health services. The Health Service Delivery Flagship expands the capacity of Jordan's health system by increasing efficiency and effectiveness in the public and private sectors. USAID has introduced an integrated package of services to meet the needs of beneficiaries in a holistic manner and provided continuous and easy-to-navigate healthcare. USAID improves providers' behavior and clinical competency and strengthens management capacity, while assisting the Ministry of Health in the design and implementation of a national system to reduce maternal deaths. By leveraging multiple community platforms and using innovative grants, USAID reaches target populations where they live and connects them with appropriate care. This activity advances ICS Mission Objective 3.1 (which incorporates the USAID Country Development Cooperation Strategy Development Objective 3) to improve Jordan's ability to deliver essential services in the health, education, and water sectors.....
